<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12043g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12043g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12043g"> 43(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> mass (penal) said on / cromlech ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">By God&apos;s Providence the faith of Erin was put to the test, and tried in the crucible. The foe and the stranger visited the peaceful shores of Erin <font color="green">[&ldquo;]</font> No church or altar was left in the land; the holy Sacrifice was offered at night, or at dawn of day, in the bog or on the mountain; a rude stone serving as an altar, and the canopy the vast expanse of the heavens. Some priests found shelter in the homes of their faithful flock; but the great majority were put to the sword or exiled. The same price was laid upon the head of a wolf or friar. <small> Very Rev. Dean Kinane, <a name="TKSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TKSP"><cite title="source">St. Patrick: his life, his heroic virtues, his labours, and the fruits of his labours</cite></a>, (ed. unknown) 184-5</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12030a" href="c12all.htm#c12030a">VI.C.12:030(a)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
